data.text:
The Arab world is massive & disparate, but the first majority Muslim country to reach the semi-finals is colossal. 

A piece on that topic here - ⁦@MezahiMaher⁩, ⁦@Levyninho⁩ & ⁦@MinaFootball⁩ did the thinking, I did the typing https://t.co/mwe1vL2GWE
Amazing that in all likelihood none of this would’ve happened if Morocco hadn’t sacked the coach that qualified them a couple of months before the tournament.
@GraceOnFootball The Wout Ball

I know advanced scouting systems & analytics etc make for better run clubs, but I miss the mindset where some manager would watch this World Cup & say “yeah, why not give Soufiane Boufal another go in the Prem”

Some say we’re a nation of pessimists, but personally I won’t hear of it. https://t.co/2Msxv13n26

Grant Wahl was an enthusiast. Impossible not to warm to someone like that even if you didn’t know them. Reading dozens of stories this morning about him helping people he had no need to help, or just being kind. Journalism, the world is diminished now someone like that is gone.

The thing about having someone good first up isn’t just a punditry platitude: only once in World Cups has a team gone 1-0 down in a shootout & won. Miss your first & for the most part you’re banjaxed.
Forgot to mention in the piece that ‘having a keeper who’s really good at saving penalties’ is also a recommended tactic.
